Pago 45, 1. 14. Ubi nimio fulsit honore, etc. Compare what Knyghton, 2 552, says (not, however, referring to this particular occasion), as regards Mortimer’s pride : ‘Illis diebus regina Isabella et Rogerus de Mortuo mari unanimi assensu appro- priaverunt sibi regalem potestatem in multis et regni thesaurum, et subpedita- verunt regem in tanturn, quod non erat quisquam qui pro regis aut regni commodo loqui auderet, quod si quis faceret, in magnam ignominiam sui persecutus est ab eis. Multa et gravia onera patriae intulerunt; et semper simul in uno hospitio hospitati sunt, unde multa obloquia et murmura de eis suspectuosa oriuntur. In tantum isti duo, regina et Rogerus, asciverunt sibi potestatem, quod comes Lancastriae Henricus‚ qui deputatus et ordinatus est capitalis custos et supremus consiliarius regis, in tempore coronationis, per communem assensum procerum et magnatum regni, pro meliori gubernaculo regis et regni, non potuit ei appropin- quare nec quicquam consilium dare!

The Brute chronicle (Harley MS. 2279) has the following: ‘And now shul ye here os sir Roger Pe Mortymer of Wygemore‚ Pat desirede and coveytede to bene atte an hie state, so Pat Pe kyng grauntid him to ben callede Pe erle of Pe Marche thurgh alle his lordeship. And he become Po so proude and so hauten that he wolde lese and forsake Pe name Pat his aunceters had evere before, and for Pat incheson he lete him calle erle of the Marche‚ and none of Pe comonis os Engelonde durste call him by none oPer name, fbr he was callede so by Pe kynges crie, Pat men shulde calle him erle of Pe Marche. And Pe Mortymere Po bore him so hauten and so proute, Pat wonder hit was to wite 3 and also disgisede him with wonder riche clothes, oute of almaner reson both of shapyng and of weryng. Wherof Pe Englisshe rnen had grete wonder how and in what maner he mute contreve or fynde suche maner pride. And Pei seiden among-es hem alle comonly Pat his pride shulde nou3te longe endure. Pago 46, 1. 16. Occiderant Hugonem de Turpintone. A pardon was issued to Edward Bohun and others for the slaying of Hugh de Turpington and Richard de Monmouth ‘ qui una cum Rogero de Mortuo mari, comite Marchiae, resistebant dicto Edwardo,' ete-calend. Rot. Patent. (4 Edw. iii.), 108.
